PATCH for passengerController.js
=================================

LOCATION 1: Change import (line 1)
----------------------------------

OLD:
const Location = require("../models/Location");

NEW:
const Bus = require("../models/Bus");


LOCATION 2: Update query (lines 15-27)
--------------------------------------

OLD CODE:
    const buses = await Location.find({
      location: {
        $near: {
          $geometry: {
            type: "Point",
            coordinates: [longitude, latitude],
          },
          $maxDistance: radiusMeters,
        },
      },
    })
      .select("busId lat lng speed source updatedAt -_id")
      .lean();

NEW CODE:
    const buses = await Bus.find({
      location: {
        $near: {
          $geometry: {
            type: "Point",
            coordinates: [longitude, latitude],
          },
          $maxDistance: radiusMeters,
        },
      },
      status: "active",
      lastUpdate: { $gte: new Date(Date.now() - 5 * 60 * 1000) }, // Active in last 5 min
    })
      .select("busId latitude longitude speed source lastUpdate -_id")
      .lean();


WHY THIS CHANGE
---------------
- Location model and Bus model now have the same geospatial "location" field
- But Location model doesn't have "status" field
- Bus model has better indexing and TTL support
- This ensures consistency with /api/buses/nearby endpoint
